{{redirect|DOZ|the unit of amount|Doz}} {{Infobox language |name=Dorze |states=[[Ethiopia]] |speakers={{sigfig|20800|2}}, including 9,900 monolinguals |date=1994 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Omotic languages|Omotic]] |fam3=[[North Omotic languages|North Omotic]] |fam4=[[Ometo languages|Ometo]] |fam5=North |iso3=doz |glotto=dorz1235 |glottorefname=Dorze }} '''Dorze''' is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in the [[Gamo Gofa Zone]] of [[Ethiopia]].<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed. 2005. [http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=doz "Dorze", ''Ethnologue: Languages of the World'']. 15th edition. Dallas: Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref> Alemayehu Abebe reports that while performing preliminary fieldwork in 1992, he found 14 [[kebele]]s in [[Chencha (woreda)|Chencha]] [[woreda]] with Dorze speakers.<ref>Alemayehu Abebe, [http://www.sil.org/silesr/2002/SILESR2002-068.pdf "Ometo Dialect Pilot Survey Report"] SIL Electronic Survey Reports SILESR 2002-068</ref>
