{{Infobox Islands |name = Misool |image_name = ID Misool.PNG |image_caption = Location of Misool |map_image = Maluku Islands en.png |native_name = |native_name_link = |location = [[South East Asia]] |coordinates= |archipelago = [[Raja Ampat Islands]] |total_islands = |major_islands = |area_km2 = |rank = 205 |highest_mount = |elevation_m =561 |country = [[Indonesia]] |population = |population_as_of = | density_km2 = |ethnic_groups = }} [[File:RajaAmpatNep9.jpg|thumb|Aerial traps of the [[pitcher plant]] [[Nepenthes sp. Misool|''Nepenthes'' sp. Misool]].]] '''Misool''', formerly spelled '''Mysol''' (Dutch: Misoöl), is one of the four major islands in the [[Raja Ampat Islands]] in [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]] (formerly [[Irian Jaya]]), [[Indonesia]]. Its area is 2,034&nbsp;km². The highest point is 561 m<ref>[http://islands.unep.ch/IHB.htm#662 ISLAND DIRECTORY. UN SYSTEM-WIDE EARTHWATCH Web Site.]</ref> and the main towns are [[Waigama]], located on the island's northern coast, and [[Lilinta]].
The inhabitants speak the [[Biga language]] and [[Matbat language]], as well as [[Indonesian language|Indonesian]].<ref>[https://www.ethnologue.com/language/bhc Ethnologue - Biga]</ref><ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/language/xmt Ethnologue - Matbat]</ref>
Other main islands of this group off the western end of West Papua are [[Salawati]], [[Batanta]] and [[Waigeo]], and there are numerous smaller islands such as [[Kofiau]].<ref>[http://indonesianhistory.info/map/malukuc15-17.html Traditional kingdoms of Maluku, early 15th century, and the spheres of influence of Ternate and Tidore, early 16th century]</ref>
==Fauna== *''[[Echymipera kalubu]]'', Common Spiny Bandicoot *''[[Echymipera rufescens]]'' *''[[Dorcopsis muelleri]]'' *''[[Phalanger orientalis]]'' *''[[Spilocuscus maculatus]]'' *''[[Petaurus breviceps]]'' *''[[Macroglossus minimus]]'' *''[[Melanotaenia flavipinnis]]'' and ''[[Melanotaenia misoolensis]]'', Misool rainbowfish<ref>Allen, G.R., Hadiaty, R.K. & Unmack, P.J. (2014): ''Melanotaenia flavipinnis'', a new species of Rainbowfish (Melanotaeniidae) from Misool Island, West Papua Province, Indonesia, ''aqua, International Journal of Ichthyology, 20 (1): 35-52.''</ref><ref>Allen, G. 1996. [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/13067/all Melanotaenia misoolensis]. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 4 August 2007.</ref> *''[[Nyctimene aello]]'' *''[[Pteropus conspicillatus]]'' *''[[Aselliscus tricuspidatus]]'' *''[[Pipistrellus papuanus]]'' *''[[Paradisasea minor]],'' Lesser Bird-of-Paradise
==History== Part of the Dutch colonial empire, the [[Netherlands East Indies]].
Occupied on 1942 by the Japanese. [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] base until 1945.<ref>No. 92 of the [[Japanese Monographs]] — "Southwest Area Naval Operations, Apr. 1942 – Apr. 1944", 10 September 1947.</ref>
