{{distinguish|University of Benin (Nigeria)}} {{Infobox university | name = University of Abomey-Calavi | native_name = Université d'Abomey-Calavi | image_name = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | motto = | mottoeng = | established = | closed = | type = | affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | rector = | principal = | dean = | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Abomey-Calavi]] | state = | province = | country = [[Benin]] | coor = {{coord|6.441|N|2.352|E|type:edu_region:BJ|display=inline,title}} | campus = | former_names = Université du Dahomey | free_label = | free = | colors = | colours = | athletics = | sports = | nickname = | mascot = | affiliations = | website = http://www.uac.bj/ | logo = | footnotes = }}
The '''University of Abomey-Calavi''' ''({{fr}} Université d'Abomey-Calavi)'' is the principal [[university]] in the country of [[Benin]], in [[Abomey-Calavi]]. The school is composed of 19 institutions and six campuses.
==History== [[File:Université d'Abomey-Calavi.jpg|thumb|300px|Main campus of Université d'Abomey-Calavi]] The university was founded in 1970 as the Université du Dahomey.<ref> Mathurin C. Houngnikpo, Samuel Decalo, ''Historical Dictionary of Benin'', Rowman & Littlefield, USA, 2013, p.151</ref> <ref> Amadou Diallo, Jérôme Aloko-N'Guessan et Kokou Henri Motcho, ''Villes et organisation de l'espace en Afrique'', KARTHALA Éditions, France, 2010, p.109</ref> In 1975 the name was changed to Université Nationale du Bénin. In 2001, the university took its current name. <ref>Université d'Abomey-Calavi, [http://www.uac.bj/web/index.php?id=377 Historique de L'UAC], uac.bj, Benin, Retrieved September 15, 2018</ref> Enrollment at UAC was over 16,000 in 1999, including over 3,300 women.
==Schools== The Université d'Abomey-Calavi is located in [[Abomey-Calavi]]. Constituent institutions of the UAC include:
* Ecole Polytechnique d’Abomey-Calavi (EPAC) * Institut des Langues Arabes et de Cultures Islamique (ILACI) * Institut Universitaire de Technologie (IUT) & Ecole Normale Supérieure de l’Enseignement Technique (ENSET) de Lokossa * Institut Régional de Santé Publique (IRSP) * Ecole Normale Supérieure (ENS) * Ecole Nationale d’Economie Appliquée et de Management (ENEAM) * Ecole Nationale d’Administration et de Magistrature (ENAM) * Institut de Mathématiques et de Sciences Physiques (IMSP) (Formation Doctorale) * Institut National de la Jeunesse de l’Education Physique et du Sport (INJEPS) * Faculté des Sciences Agronomiques (FSA) * Faculté des Lettres, Arts et Sciences Humaines (FLASH) * Faculté des Sciences de la Santé (FSS) * Faculté des Sciences Economiques (FASEG) * Faculté de Droit et de Sciences Politiques (FADESP) * Faculté des Sciences et Techniques (FAST)
